Don't know about the US but in Poland "opony zimowe" (winter tires) is the only term in use. Their purpose is to improve handling and traction on snow though (as no tire by itself helps with the other winter woe, ice). 

I was late in changing tires on my Mustang one year and I ended up having to drive all across Warsaw on summer tires in a December snowstorm (I stupidly decided to visit my father with the Mustang rather than my sensible and already winter-shod Volkswagen). Jesus. It was one of the most stressful things I experienced in my life. The next day I bought the best winter tires they had at the tire shop 🤣. Bless you, Michelin.

